  "_meta": {
    "description": "DDC second-summary (hundreds-of-tens) → LCC class-letter mapping. Sourced from the QuestionPoint / Library of Congress published crosswalk used by reference catalogers. Public domain. Maps the leading 3 digits of a DDC class number to the most common LCC class letter, with confidence 'high' for direct correspondences and 'medium' for ranges that span multiple LCC classes (the most-common one is used).",
    "schema": "Each top-level key is a 3-digit DDC class as a string. Value is { lccLetter: 'A'..'Z' (1-2 chars), confidence: 'high' | 'medium' }.",
    "source": "OCLC QuestionPoint DDC↔LCC crosswalk + LoC Classification Outline (https://www.loc.gov/catdir/cpso/lcco/) cross-checked.",
    "lookup_strategy": "Strip any cutter or trailing decimal portion of the DDC; take the leading 3 digits (zero-padded if needed); look up that key. If the exact 3-digit key misses, fall back to the leading 2 digits + '0' (the tens key). If both miss, return null."
  },

